•
Posted @withregram • @prettypeachesbynina Hyper-dilute Radiesse + Vollure + Botox 

What is bio stimulation? These products include sculptra, #radiesse, or PDO threads. Each one is placed into the dermis with the purpose of replacing collagen loss and aiding in skin renewal. 
Remember collagen is the building block of our skin. Each of these products is injected with the purpose of assisting fibroblasts to reproduce in your dermis (middle of the skin) create new cells, and replace lost collagen. 
This results in:
-Improving tone and creepiness of the skin 
-Increasing elasticity of the skin
-Improving accordion lines around the mouth 
-Repairing underlying skin 
-Treating fine lines and wrinkles 

Biostimulation is unlike dermal fillers. The results are not instant. They require a minimum series of 2 treatments and they need to be timed at specific intervals. I personally use skin cycles to plan treatments. Please know if you are ever told 1 treatment will provide you results you have not been educated correctly!

My go to for the lower face:
-Hyperdilute + Vollure is for my patients with lower face hollowing but overall skin health. The advantage of mixing with a soft and spreadable HA like #Vollure is the product will integrate like a fat pad and the patient will sustain volume once the gel and water absorbs. 

At the 4 week mark we always add a targeted energy source, either our yag laser or #RF microneedling, in order to increase fibroblast production. More fibroblasts means more collagen production which means better + faster results for you! 
•
This is a healed result. I do not share immediate after photos with biostimulators because they are deceiving. The products have a high volume of water or gel when injected so they add significant volume increase when placed but this is always absorbed in a few days. An after photo is typically taken at 4-6 months.
